This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Justice Point Pretrial Services Violation Report received and forwarded to Judge for review.

Defendant Trystien Allen Homan in court.  Attorney William Hotchkiss in court for Trystien Allen Homan.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. Court reviewed the Justice Point Report.  Court granted defense request for status conference in Branch 11.  Court ordered defendant to remain compliant with Justice Point monitoring.
Status conference scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Trystien Allen Homan in court with Attorney William Hotchkiss; both appear by video.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Shorewood Officer J. Santiago. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 11.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 15, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.

CASE HEARD OFF THE RECORD DUE TO TECHNICAL DIFFICULTIES:  
Defendant Trystien Allen Homan in court with attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz.  Defendant Trystien Allen Homan in custody.  Julie D Knyszek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   All parties appeared by video conference.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Judge Franke, Branch 25.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
